ising and reception of key films, the book offers unique insight into a cinematic remembering that was a product of the studio system as it emerged as a global entertainment industry.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aCollective memory and motion pictures. 0aHistorical filmszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aMotion pictureszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aWar filmszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xMotion pictures and the war. 4aAmerican Studies : American Culture. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Film Studies. 4aHistory : American History. 4aHistory : European History. 4aHistory : History. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847698840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438476988423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438476988/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles